# Application Architecture

Important: I do NOT want to include a Domain Layer. Please don’t include a domain layer and Use Cases unless instructed otherwise.

Important: I want the top level packaging to be feature based. So the first package will be articles. Inside the articles package I want only 3 packages: ui, presentation and data.

* UI Layer
- Single Activity app with Composables
- Navigation components

* Presentation Layer
- ViewModels
- UI State classes
- Presentation models, e.g., Article

* Data Layer
- Repository Implementations
- Remote Data Source (API)
- Data Models, e.g., ArticleData
- NO database or local storage need
- Repository Pattern. No Interface, only repository implementation. Single source of truth. Easy to switch data sources

* MVVM Pattern
- ViewModels handle UI logic and UI state
- Composables are responsible only for UI
- State classes represent UI state

* Dependency Injection
- We'll use Hilt for dependency injection

* Coroutines & State Flow
- Coroutines for asynchronous operations
- Handle API calls and data processing
- State Flow between ViewModel and UI to manage UI state updates

* Key concepts
- Clean Architecture
- Important: Simplicity
- Separation of concerns
- Testability
- Maintainability
- I don't want you to create any base classes

